 Hon newspcipe o iarnrur irctfc Editor That Tells State laton and opinion with raori News Weekly fhap 1000ft readers VOLUME XXIII THE WEEKLY ECHO FRIDAY MARCH 29 1946 _XI MB1K M The amnion Defenst I For Trnerations Yet Unburn April 12th marks the first anniver sary of the death of Franklin Delano Roosevelt Mr Roosevelt had his political ene mies as indeed every great president of this country before him had his j But on this first anniversary of his death friend and foe alike can join in acclaiming what Mr Roosevelt said in a memorable address about the meaning of America for us and for all mankind For more than three centuries we Americans have been building on this continent a free society A society in which the promise of the human spirit may find fulfillment Com mingled here are the blood and gen ius of all the peoples of the world who have sought this promis We have built well We are con tinuing our efforts to bring the bless ings of a free society of a free and productive economic system to every family in the land This is"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-03T13:43:07.881Z", "group": ["ndnp/msar", "mississippi-department-of-archives-and-history"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88067047/1946-03-29/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:msar:batch_msar_hematite_ver01:data:sn88067047:00383344669:1946032901:0446/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=395&w=294", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:msar:batch_msar_hematite_ver01:data:sn88067047:00383344669:1946032901:0446/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=791&w=589", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_hematite_ver01/data/sn88067047/00383344669/1946032901/0446.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["meridian", "lauderdale", "united states", "mississippi"], "location_city": ["meridian"], "location_country": ["united states"], 